                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/14275: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-23T00:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 23, 1941—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received August 23—8:20
                        p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3840. Personal for the Secretary of State. This morning I talked with Mr. Eden.
                    He wanted you to know how seriously they view the <pb facs="0419" n="411"
                        xml:id="pg_411"/> German agents in Iran. The British are certain that their
                    negotiations with the Iran Government are being directed by the Germans. I felt
                    Mr. Eden was simply asking for a sympathetic understanding of their problem.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
